is to help UIC researchers and scholars identify appropriate funding opportunities, form effective teams, and craft winning proposals, with the ultimate goal of increasing the quality and quantity of externally-funded research and scholarly activity at UIC.       Find funding      RDS manages resources and provides tools to support your faculty research including:   Current OVCR/UIC Internal Funding  Authorization to apply to a one per institution “limited submission” grant opportunity  Grants Databases to match your expertise with compatible funding opportunities – Learn more or enter a key word below to do a quick search right now!       Research Development Services        Limited Competitions          Funding Announcements          Proposal Development          RDSNews          Pivot          Seed Funding           Announcement and Deadlines       Information for Campus Research Restart    Posted on April 28, 2020        CCTS Pilot Funding for COVID-19    Posted on April 14, 2020        Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research UPDATE – Friday, March 20, 2020 - 5:25pm    Posted on March 20, 2020        Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research UPDATE – March 19, 2020, 4:25pm    Posted on March 19, 2020        COVID-19 Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research Update - March 17, 2020    Posted on March 17, 2020           May  22  2020      Data Science Lightning Talks     Friday, 10:00 am–11:00 am   WebEx      More Events             Sponsored Programs    Back to main content           Find Funding     Limited Competitions     Limited Competitions Archive      Internal Funding    External Funding    Government Relations Liaisons: Lewis-Burke/GRC/EAB    RDS Newsletter    Faculty Awards     Research and Scholarship Annual Award Competition     Researcher, Scholar, and Inventor of the Year Awards Recipients    Submission Cover Page      Awards for Creative Activity in the Fine, Performing, and Applied Arts; the Humanities; and the Social Sciences     Recipients  